  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba3\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0b85\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Cabinet approves increase in train fares",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Government has stated that the continuous losses of the Sri Lanka Railway Department due to the increase in fuel prices have increased and the inability to provide proper service.",
        "Thus, the need to revise train fares and other train fares is currently being observed.",
        "The proposal was made to increase the railway fares which have not been revised in the last 5 years and other railway fares which have not been revised in the last 14 years.",
        "In this context, the Cabinet has approved the proposal put forward by the Minister of Transport and Highways."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
        {
          "text": "Cabinet",
          "label": "ORG"
        }
      ],
      "body_line_ents_list": [
        [
          {
            "text": "the Sri Lanka Railway Department",
            "label": "FAC"
          }
        ],
        [],
        [
          {
